definition.value: A diazo compound that is L-phenylalanyl-L-phenylalanine in which the amino group is protected by a (benzyloxy)carbonyl group and the carboxy group is substituted by a diazoacetyl group. It is a cathepsin L inhibitor.
The dipeptide obtained by coupling N-benzyloxycarbonyl-L-tyrosine with the hydroxamic acid derivative of L-leucine. It is an inhibitor of the metallo-protease enzyme, pseudolysin (EC 3.4.24.36).
